A general view of the outside of a COVID-19 ward at  Hospital in Cape Town. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa has recorded 5,451 new COVID-19 infections in the last 24 hours. A further 97 people have died due to the virus, bringing total fatalities to 56,929. READ: COVID-19 in SA: Taxi drivers get training The country currently has a 93.2 percent recovery rate. More than 40,000 tests have been conducted since the last report.